The paper deals with preference elicitation in multiagent systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of trees as a domain for single peaked preferences suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of query complexity is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI), which further supports these categories as likely choices.
